      "writtenOn": "2021-05-02T16:11:49Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e This still doesn\u0027t work if you get to the playlist from the WPS hotkey :(\n\u003e \n\u003e Turns out on further investigation, the hotkey and ACTION_WPS_VIEW_PLAYLIST keybinding do not actually enter the playlist viewer as a sub-activity. Instead, they pop the WPS activity and the root menu code handles popping back to the WPS when the list is finished... who\u0027d have guessed?\n\nThat\u0027s... really disappointing? What\u0027s the point of even having the activity stack if you\u0027re just going to go in one direction as far as the user can see and go the other direction for bookkeeping? Sigh...\n\nIt looks like the playlist is indeed null whenever it\u0027s dealing with the current active playlist, regardless of whether it was loaded from a playlist or just saved to a file. Or, at least it is in all the scenarios I could think to look at. I just printed out whether or not the playlist was null in the simulator.\n\nIt just seems like \"there\u0027s no way it could have been that easy.\"\n\nAnyway, yeah it seems to work just fine, so it should be fixed in next patchset.",
      "parentUuid": "5e3c1646_4db855d5",
      "revId": "7049fdcf61b48c9f1c5b7cea868d95157ef51f9d",
      "serverId": "583131e1-1a33-4f2b-b8ec-82434880f207",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
