      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e Suggest rewriting this whole segment a bit. Right now if temp \u003d \"Playlists/foo\" is entered, then directoryonly \u003d \"Playlists\" and the reload fails.\n\u003e \n\u003e I\u0027m thinking something along these lines:\n\u003e \n\u003e   char directoryonly[MAX_PATH+3];\n\u003e   directoryonly[0] \u003d \u0027/\u0027; // hack: prepending two slashes simplifies the code\n\u003e   directoryonly[1] \u003d \u0027/\u0027;\n\u003e   strcpy(directoryonly+2, temp);\n\nThe only thing I\u0027m unsure about, is why prepend two slashes? Wouldn\u0027t one be sufficient?\n\n\u003e   char* filename \u003d strrchr(directoryonly, \u0027/\u0027);\n\u003e   *filename \u003d \u0027\\0\u0027;\n\u003e   filename +\u003d 1;\n\nI think this effectively does the same thing as what I\u0027m already doing with the \"path_slash\" variable, I might play around with it and see what\u0027s easier to read though, I had to sit and look at these three lines for a while before I really got what they did.",
